          </interactive>
      </figure>
    </exploration>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="Subsection-Vector-Subtraction">
    <title>Vector Subtraction</title>
    <p>
      We can find the difference of two vectors by interpreting subtraction as ``addition of the opposite".  Thus,
      <me>
        \mathbf{v}-\mathbf{u}=\mathbf{v}+(-\mathbf{u})
      </me>
      Vector subtraction has an interesting geometric interpretation.  As shown in the figure below, if <m>\mathbf{v}+\mathbf{u}</m> is a diagonal of the parallelogram determined by <m>\mathbf{v}</m> and <m>\mathbf{u}</m>, the difference <m>\mathbf{v}-\mathbf{u}</m> is the other diagonal of the same parallelogram.
    </p>
